      • createGraph

        public java.lang.String createGraph(java.lang.String nameStr,
                                    java.lang.String creationTypeStr,
                                    java.lang.String graphInputFormatStr,
                                    java.lang.String doMakeUndirectedStr,
                                    java.lang.String contentStr)
        Imports a graph.
        Parameters:
        nameStr - The name for the graph.
        creationTypeStr - The creation type the graph was created by.
        graphInputFormatStr - The name of the graph input format.
        doMakeUndirectedStr - Optional query parameter. Defines whether directed edges shall be turned into undirected edges (TRUE) or not.
        contentStr - The graph input.
        Returns:
        A graph id xml. Or an error xml.

      • getGraphs

        public java.lang.String getGraphs(java.lang.String firstIndexStr,
                                  java.lang.String lengthStr,
                                  java.lang.String includeMetaStr,
                                  java.lang.String executionStatusesStr)
        Returns the ids (or meta information) of multiple graphs.
        Parameters:
        firstIndexStr - Optional query parameter. The result list index of the first id to return. Defaults to 0.
        lengthStr - Optional query parameter. The number of ids to return. Defaults to Long.MAX_VALUE.
        includeMetaStr - Optional query parameter. If TRUE, instead of the ids the META XML of each graph is returned. Defaults to FALSE.
        executionStatusesStr - Optional query parameter. If set only those graphs are returned whose creation method has one of the given ExecutionStatus names. Multiple status names are separated using the "-" delimiter.
        Returns:
        The graphs. Or an error xml.

      • deleteGraph

        public java.lang.String deleteGraph(java.lang.String graphIdStr)
        Deletes a graph. All covers based on the graph are removed as well. If a benchmark is currently calculating the graph the execution is terminated. If an algorithm is currently calculating a cover based on the graph it is terminated. If a metric is currently running on a cover based on the grap it is terminated.
        Parameters:
        graphIdStr - The graph id.
        Returns:
        A confirmation xml. Or an error xml.

      • createCover

        public java.lang.String createCover(java.lang.String graphIdStr,
                                    java.lang.String nameStr,
                                    java.lang.String creationTypeStr,
                                    java.lang.String coverInputFormatStr,
                                    java.lang.String contentStr)
        Imports a cover for an existing graph.
        Parameters:
        graphIdStr - The id of the graph that the cover is based on.
        nameStr - A name for the cover.
        creationTypeStr - The creation type the cover was created by.
        coverInputFormatStr - The name of the input format.
        contentStr - The cover input.
        Returns:
        A cover id xml. Or an error xml.

      • getCovers

        public java.lang.String getCovers(java.lang.String firstIndexStr,
                                  java.lang.String lengthStr,
                                  java.lang.String includeMetaStr,
                                  java.lang.String executionStatusesStr,
                                  java.lang.String metricExecutionStatusesStr,
                                  java.lang.String graphIdStr)
        Returns the ids (or meta information) of multiple covers.
        Parameters:
        firstIndexStr - Optional query parameter. The result list index of the first id to return. Defaults to 0.
        lengthStr - Optional query parameter. The number of ids to return. Defaults to Long.MAX_VALUE.
        includeMetaStr - Optional query parameter. If TRUE, instead of the ids the META XML of each graph is returned. Defaults to FALSE.
        executionStatusesStr - Optional query parameter. If set only those covers are returned whose creation method status corresponds to one of the given ExecutionStatus names. Multiple status names are separated using the "-" delimiter.
        metricExecutionStatusesStr - Optional query parameter. If set only those covers are returned that have a corresponding metric log with a status corresponding to one of the given ExecutionStatus names. Multiple status names are separated using the "-" delimiter.
        graphIdStr - Optional query parameter. If set only those covers are returned that are based on the corresponding graph.
        Returns:
        The covers. Or an error xml.

      • deleteCover

        public java.lang.String deleteCover(java.lang.String coverIdStr,
                                    java.lang.String graphIdStr)
        Deletes a cover. If the cover is still being created by an algorithm, the algorithm is terminated. If the cover is still being created by a ground truth benchmark, the benchmark is terminated and the corresponding graph is deleted as well. If metrics are running on the cover, they are terminated.
        Parameters:
        coverIdStr - The cover id.
        graphIdStr - The graph id of the graph corresponding the cover.
        Returns:
        A confirmation xml. Or an error xml.

      • runAlgorithm

        public java.lang.String runAlgorithm(java.lang.String graphIdStr,
                                     java.lang.String nameStr,
                                     java.lang.String creationTypeStr,
                                     java.lang.String content,
                                     java.lang.String componentNodeCountFilterStr,
                                     java.lang.String contentWeighting)
        Creates a new cover by running an algorithm on an existing graph.
        Parameters:
        graphIdStr - The id of the graph to run the algorithm on, must have the creation method status completed.
        nameStr - The name for the cover.
        creationTypeStr - The name of a cover creation type corresponding to an ocd algorithm. Defines the algorithm to execute.
        content - A parameter xml defining any non-default parameters passed to the algorithm.
        componentNodeCountFilterStr - Option query parameter. The component node count filter applied by the OcdAlgorithmExecutor.
        Returns:
        The id of the cover being calculated which is reserved for the algorithm result. Or an error xml.

      • runGroundTruthBenchmark

        public java.lang.String runGroundTruthBenchmark(java.lang.String coverNameStr,
                                                java.lang.String graphNameStr,
                                                java.lang.String creationTypeStr,
                                                java.lang.String contentStr)
        Creates a ground truth benchmark cover.
        Parameters:
        coverNameStr - The name for the cover.
        graphNameStr - The name for the underlying benchmark graph.
        creationTypeStr - The name of a graph creation type corresponding a ground truth benchmark.
        contentStr - A parameter xml defining any non-default parameters passed to the benchmark.
        Returns:
        The id of the cover being calculated which is reserved for the benchmark result (contains also the id of the graph being calculated which is reserved for the benchmark result as well). Or an error xml.

      • runStatisticalMeasure

        public java.lang.String runStatisticalMeasure(java.lang.String coverIdStr,
                                              java.lang.String graphIdStr,
                                              java.lang.String metricTypeStr,
                                              java.lang.String contentStr)
        Runs a statistical measure on a cover and creates the corresponding log.
        Parameters:
        coverIdStr - The id of the cover, must have the creation method status completed.
        graphIdStr - The id of the graph corresponding to the cover.
        metricTypeStr - A metric type corresponding to a statistical measure.
        contentStr - A parameter xml defining any non-default parameters passed to the metric.
        Returns:
        The id of the metric log being calculated which is reserved for the metric result (contains also the corresponding cover and graph id). Or an error xml.

      • runKnowledgeDrivenMeasure

        public java.lang.String runKnowledgeDrivenMeasure(java.lang.String coverIdStr,
                                                  java.lang.String graphIdStr,
                                                  java.lang.String metricTypeStr,
                                                  java.lang.String groundTruthCoverIdStr,
                                                  java.lang.String contentStr)
        Runs a knowledge-driven measure on a cover and creates the corresponding log.
        Parameters:
        coverIdStr - The id of the cover, must have the creation method status completed.
        graphIdStr - The id of the graph corresponding to the cover.
        metricTypeStr - A metric type corresponding to a knowledge-driven measure.
        groundTruthCoverIdStr - The id of the ground truth cover used by the metric, must have the creation method status completed. The ground truth cover's corresponding graph must be the same as the one corresponding to the first cover.
        contentStr - A parameter xml defining any non-default parameters passed to the algorithm.
        Returns:
        The id of the metric log being calculated which is reserved for the metric result (contains also the corresponding cover and graph id). Or an error xml.
